\[Gamma], \[Delta]}, {a, b}] finds a vector x that minimizes the linear \
fractional function (\[Alpha] . x + \[Beta])/(\[Gamma] . x + \[Delta]) \
subject to the linear inequality constraints a . x + b \[SucceedsEqual] 0. \
LinearFractionalOptimization[{\[Alpha], \[Beta], \[Gamma], \[Delta]}, {a, b}, \
{a  , b  }] includes the linear equality constraints a   . x + b   \
\[LongEqual] 0.LinearFractionalOptimization[{\[Alpha], \[Beta], \[Gamma], \
\[Delta]}, \[Ellipsis], {dom , dom , \[Ellipsis]}] takes x  to be in the \
domain dom , where dom  is Integers or Reals. LinearFractionalOptimization[\
\[Ellipsis], \"prop\"] specifies what solution property \"prop\" should be \
returned.\n                                                                   \
