                 "label" -> "LinearProgramming", "kind" -> 3, "detail" -> 
                  "System Symbol", "documentation" -> 
                  "LinearProgramming[c, m, b] finds a vector x that minimizes \
the quantity c . x subject to the constraints m . x \[GreaterEqual] b and x \
\[GreaterEqual] 0. LinearProgramming[c, m, {{b , s }, {b , s }, \[Ellipsis]}] \
finds a vector x that minimizes c . x subject to x \[GreaterEqual] 0 and \
linear constraints specified by the matrix m and the pairs {b , s }. For each \
row m  of m, the corresponding constraint is m  . x \[GreaterEqual] b  if s  \
== 1, or m  . x == b  if s  == 0, or m  . x \[LessEqual] b  if s  == -1. \
LinearProgramming[c, m, b, l] minimizes c . x subject to the constraints \
specified by m and b and x \[GreaterEqual] l. LinearProgramming[c, m, b, {l , \
l , \[Ellipsis]}] minimizes c . x subject to the constraints specified by m \
and b and x  \[GreaterEqual] l . LinearProgramming[c, m, b, {{l , u }, {l , u \
}, \[Ellipsis]}] minimizes c . x subject to the constraints specified by m \
