                  "FunctionBijective[f, x] tests whether f(x) \[LongEqual] y \
has exactly one solution x \[Element] Reals for each y \[Element] \
Reals.FunctionBijective[f, x, dom] tests whether f(x) \[LongEqual] y has \
exactly one solution x \[Element] dom for each y \[Element] \
dom.FunctionBijective[{f , f , \[Ellipsis]}, {x , x , \[Ellipsis]}, dom] \
tests whether f (x , x , \[Ellipsis]) \[LongEqual] y , f (x , x , \
\[Ellipsis]) \[LongEqual] y , \[Ellipsis] has exactly one solution x , x , \
\[Ellipsis] \[Element] dom for each y , y , \[Ellipsis] \[Element] \
dom.FunctionBijective[{funs, xcons, ycons}, xvars, yvars, dom] tests whether \
funs(xvars) \[LongEqual] yvars has exactly one solution with xvars \[Element] \
dom restricted by the constraints xcons for each yvars \[Element] dom \
restricted by the constraints ycons. \n                                       \
